Document: AudioEffectChorus
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectchorus.rst
Summary: This section details the properties available for configuring the AudioEffectChorus, including dry/wet mix and individual voice parameters.

dry (float): The volume ratio of the original audio. Value can range from 0 to 1. Default: 1.0.
Method: set_dry(value: float)
Method: get_dry()

Properties for individual chorus voices (1-4):

voice/X/cutoff_hz (float): The frequency threshold of the voice's low-pass filter in Hz. Default: 8000.0 (for voices 1 and 2).
Method: set_voice_cutoff_hz(voice_idx: int, cutoff_hz: float)
Method: get_voice_cutoff_hz(voice_idx: int)

voice/X/delay_ms (float): The delay of the voice in milliseconds, compared to the original audio. Default: 15.0 (for voice 1), 20.0 (for voice 2).
Method: set_voice_delay_ms(voice_idx: int, delay_ms: float)
Method: get_voice_delay_ms(voice_idx: int)

voice/X/depth_ms (float): The depth of the voice's low-frequency oscillator in milliseconds. Default: 2.0 (for voice 1), 3.0 (for voice 2).
Method: set_voice_depth_ms(voice_idx: int, depth_ms: float)
Method: get_voice_depth_ms(voice_idx: int)

voice/X/level_db (float): The gain of the voice in dB. Default: 0.0 (for voices 1 and 2).
Method: set_voice_level_db(voice_idx: int, level_db: float)
Method: get_voice_level_db(voice_idx: int)

voice/X/pan (float): The pan position of the voice. Default: -0.5 (for voice 1), 0.5 (for voice 2).
Method: set_voice_pan(voice_idx: int, pan: float)
Method: get_voice_pan(voice_idx: int)

voice/X/rate_hz (float): The rate of the voice's low-frequency oscillator in Hz. Default: 0.8 (for voice 1), 1.2 (for voice 2).
Method: set_voice_rate_hz(voice_idx: int, rate_hz: float)
Method: get_voice_rate_hz(voice_idx: int)

voice_count (int): The number of voices in the effect. Value can range from 1 to 4. Default: 2.
Method: set_voice_count(value: int)
Method: get_voice_count()

wet (float): The volume ratio of all voices. Value can range from 0 to 1. Default: 0.5.
Method: set_wet(value: float)
Method: get_wet()
